    <description>A large, green humanoid with elephant-like tusks, Beets are a strange, heavyset, bipedal being capable of gathering some of their nutrition from photosynthesizing with the sun, and they must be exposed to a certain degree of sunlight to survive. Unclear whether friendly or not.\n \n Beets are not plants, although they have evolved many plantlike properties. Their ability to photosynthesize does not fully satiate them. This is partially because of the fact that Beets do not respirate like plants; they breathe in oxygen and breathe out carbon dioxide. The skin of Beets is naturally thick and serves as armor inherent to their body. Their "meat" is a strange substance similar to cellulose and fiber, making it closer to vegetable than flesh. \n \n While Beets do exist in Core Worlds and elsewhere, they are most common on the Rim, where they are believed to have originated. On Rim Worlds such as this, Beets are most commonly found in two different civilizations.</description>
